Author: hanhansal
Text: I get how you feel. I think we feel this way because we're scared of becoming like them? Or because we see ourselves in them? Idk

Author: lost12
Text: You shouldn't feel bad about changing first. Your friend may never change. That's a sad reality. Consider people in a crack house. One of them finally becomes drug-free. Should that person feel bad they were the first one that became drug-free while their friends still addicted?  Thinking about someone stuffing an entire pie would be a trigger for anyone :(
